<h1>DIY Project: Build a Wooden Bookshelf</h1>

<h2>Steps:</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Measure and cut the wooden boards to desired dimensions.</li>
    <li>Assemble the frame of the bookshelf using screws and wood glue.</li>
    <li>Attach the shelves to the frame using screws.</li>
    <li>Sand the bookshelf to smooth out any rough edges.</li>
    <li>Apply a coat of wood stain or paint for finishing.</li>
    <li>Let the bookshelf dry completely before use.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Materials and Quantities:</h2>
<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Material</th>
        <th>Quantity</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Wooden boards (pine)</td>
        <td>6 pieces</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Screws (2-inch)</td>
        <td>24 pieces</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Wood glue</td>
        <td>1 bottle</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Sandpaper (medium grit)</td>
        <td>1 sheet</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Wood stain or paint</td>
        <td>1 can</td>
    </tr>
</table>

